    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Is there any interest in supporting `numpy.seterr` and the `numpy.errstate` context manager (or equivalents) in pandas?  Could be useful to force exceptions to be raised in situations where you really don't want NaNs or don't want inf values from things being divided by zero.  If not, then perhaps a note should be added to the docs explaining that anything other than the default numpy error handling will cause problems with pandas.\n"
  },
