    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "There is an option to treat infs as nulls if you want.\n\n```\nmode.use_inf_as_null : boolean\n    True means treat None, NaN, INF, -INF as null (old way),\n    False means None and NaN are null, but INF, -INF are not null\n    (new way).\n    [default: False] [currently: False]\n```\n\nbut by definition pandas must have this set (in fact it IS set by pandas). Changing is at your own risk (and to be honest this is the first time I have seen someone have a problem with it), though I did once myself a long time ago. If you think a note somewhere in the docs would help, then ok.\n"
